You can achieve that using [async/await][1] syntax:

    initializeAllComponents(components: Agent[]) {
        for (let i = 0; i &lt; components.length; i++) {
            const agent = components[i];
            await this.componentService.setAgent(agent).catch(console.log);
            this.componentService.clearAnyOneOfIndex();
        }
    }

Be careful with `async/await`, because you need to use native `for` loop in order to wait previous call - `forEach`, `reduce` and similar methods just fires off multiple asynchronous calls.


