When you call [`jQuery.noConflict()`](https://api.jquery.com/jQuery.noConflict/), `$` variable will not be defined. 

1. Replace all uses of `$` with `jQuery`, for example:

        jQuery(&#39;#table_id&#39;).DataTable({
           // ... skipped ...
        });

2. Call jQuery.noConflict() only once, for example:

        &lt;script src=&quot;jquery.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
        &lt;script&gt;jQuery.noConflict();&lt;/script&gt;

